# Correx

**AI Correction OS** — Persistent human correction memory that makes AI learn from feedback.

Every time a human corrects AI output, the correction is captured, generalized into reusable rules, and automatically injected into future generations. The AI stops making the same mistake twice.

## How It Works

```
Human corrects AI output
       |
       v
save_conversation_turn()  -->  ConversationTurn stored
       |
       |  extract corrections
       v
PreferenceRule (candidate)     reaction_score (0.0-1.0)
       |
       |  evidence_count >= 2
       v
PreferenceRule (PROMOTED)
       |
       |  next task starts
       v
build_guidance_context()  -->  Guidance injected into prompt
       |
       v
AI generates better output
       |
       |  measure improvement
       v
record_growth()  -->  baseline vs guided delta
```

## Quick Start

```bash
pip install pseudo-intelligence-core[mcp]
pseudo-intelligence --transport stdio
```

Or with Python:

```bash
pip install pseudo-intelligence-core
python -m claude_pseudo_intelligence
```

## MCP Tools

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `build_guidance_context` | Retrieve relevant past corrections for a new task |
| `save_episode` | Save a completed task outcome |
| `save_correction` | Record a human override on an episode |
| `save_conversation_turn` | Log conversation feedback (triggers rule promotion) |
| `save_training_example` | Mark accepted output as supervised training data |
| `list_entries` | Browse episode history |
| `list_conversation_turns` | Browse conversation turn history |
| `list_preference_rules` | List promoted and candidate rules |
| `record_growth` | Record baseline vs guided quality measurement |
| `get_growth_summary` | Overall growth statistics and trend |
| `get_growth_trend` | Score history for a specific case |
| `export_training_dataset` | Generate MLX-LM compatible JSONL files |
| `run_auto_training_cycle` | Export dataset + trigger LoRA training |

## MCP Resources

| URI | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| `memory://summary` | Overview of all memory state |
| `memory://entries/{limit}` | Recent episode summaries |
| `memory://guidance/{task_scope}` | Relevant corrections for a scope |

## Configuration

### Claude Code

```bash
claude mcp add pseudo-intelligence \
  -s user \
  -- python3 -m claude_pseudo_intelligence \
  --memory-dir ~/.pseudo-intelligence \
  --transport stdio
```

### Claude Desktop

Add to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "pseudo-intelligence": {
      "command": "python3",
      "args": [
        "-m", "claude_pseudo_intelligence",
        "--memory-dir", "~/.pseudo-intelligence",
        "--transport", "stdio"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

### HTTP Transport

```bash
pseudo-intelligence \
  --memory-dir ~/.pseudo-intelligence \
  --transport streamable-http \
  --host 127.0.0.1 \
  --port 8000 \
  --path /mcp
```

## Architecture

```
src/claude_pseudo_intelligence/
  service.py              # Main facade — single entry point
  mcp_server.py           # FastMCP server (13 tools, 3 resources)
  history_store.py        # JSON-based persistent storage
  schemas.py              # Core dataclasses (5 types)
  learning_context.py     # Correction retrieval & scoring
  conversation_learning.py # Text normalization, rule extraction
  reaction_scorer.py      # Rule-based feedback scoring
  growth_tracker.py       # Before/after measurement
  training_dataset.py     # JSONL export for mlx-lm
  auto_train.py           # MLX-LM LoRA training orchestration
  secret_store.py         # macOS Keychain integration
```

### Storage

All data is stored as JSON files in the memory directory (default: `~/.pseudo-intelligence/`):

- `history.json` — Episode records (max 50)
- `conversation_history.json` — Conversation turns (max 200)
- `preference_rules.json` — Promoted and candidate rules (max 100)
- `growth/` — Growth measurement records

### Rule Promotion

Corrections are extracted from user feedback using pattern matching. When the same correction appears in 2+ conversation turns, it is promoted from `candidate` to `promoted` status and included in future guidance context.

## Training Pipeline

Export accepted outputs as supervised training data:

```bash
pseudo-intelligence-export \
  --memory-dir ~/.pseudo-intelligence \
  --output-dir ./training_data
```

Output: `train.jsonl`, `valid.jsonl`, `test.jsonl`, `preference.jsonl`, `manifest.json`

Auto-train with MLX-LM LoRA:

```bash
pip install pseudo-intelligence-core[train]
pseudo-intelligence-train \
  --model mlx-community/Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct-4bit \
  --memory-dir ~/.pseudo-intelligence \
  --output-dir ./training_artifacts
```

## Python API

```python
from claude_pseudo_intelligence.service import PseudoIntelligenceService

svc = PseudoIntelligenceService(memory_dir="~/.pseudo-intelligence")

# Get guidance for a new task
guidance = svc.build_guidance_context(
    task_title="Design landing page",
    raw_text="Create a B2B service top page",
)

# Save conversation feedback
svc.save_conversation_turn(
    task_scope="ui_design",
    user_message="Design the top page",
    assistant_message="Here is a content-heavy design...",
    user_feedback="Too much content. Add whitespace.",
)

# Check promoted rules
rules = svc.list_preference_rules(promoted_only=True)
```

